#. type: Plain text
#: debian-bullseye
msgid ""
"The argument must be in local time, even if you keep your Hardware Clock in "
"UTC.  See the B<\\%--localtime> option.  Therefore, the argument should not "
"include any timezone information.  It also should not be a relative time "
"like \"+5 minutes\", because B<\\%hwclock>'s precision depends upon "
"correlation between the argument's value and when the enter key is pressed.  "
"Fractional seconds are silently dropped.  This option is capable of "
"understanding many time and date formats, but the previous parameters should "
"be observed."
msgstr ""

